RIFT VALLEY FEVER, RUMINANTS - KENYA: OIE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 10 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Alert Message 10 Jan 2007 [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=event_summary&this_country_code=KEN&reportid=4487>

Information received on 9 Jan 2007 from Dr Joseph Omachi Musaa,
Director of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Livestock and Fisheries
Development, Department of Veterinary Services, NAIROBI, Kenya
Summary
Start date 4 Dec 2006
Date of confirmation of event 22 Dec 2006
Report date 9 Jan 2007
Date of previous occurrence September 2002
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent - Nature of diagnosis Clinical, Laboratory (basic),
Necropsy Report pertains to Entire country
New Outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak Location: NORTH-EASTERN (Galmagara, Garissa)
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Sheep / 9000 / 1500 / 105 / 0 / 0
Goats / 10 000 / 1500 / 95 / 0 / 0
Cattle / 4000 / 500 / 30 / 0 / 0
Camelidae / 4000 / 500 / 5 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species Sheep
Apparent morbidity rate 16.67 percent
Apparent mortality rate 1.17 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 7.00 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 1.17 percent
Species Goats
Apparent morbidity rate 15.00 percent
Apparent mortality rate 0.95 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 6.33 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 0.95 percent
Species Cattle
Apparent morbidity rate 12.50 percent
Apparent mortality rate 0.75 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 6.00 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 0.75 percent
Species Camelidae
Apparent morbidity rate 12.50 percent
Apparent mortality rate 0.13 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 1.00 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 0.13 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: Vectors
Control measures:
Measures already applied: Movement control inside the country;
screening; vaccination in response to the outbreak(s); dipping /
spraying; quarantine; vaccination permitted; treatment of affected
animals (antibiotics)
Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type Central Veterinary Laboratory, Kabete (Local
laboratory)
Tests and results: Species Test Test date Result
Cattle enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) 22 Dec 2006 Positive
Cattle indirect fluorescent antibody (IFA) test 22 Dec 2006 Positive
Sheep / goats enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) 22 Dec 2006 Positive
Sheep / goats indirect fluorescent antibody (IFA) test 22 Dec 2006 Positive
Laboratory name and type Kenya Agricultural Research Institute
(National laboratory)
Tests and results
Species Test Test date Result
Cattle virus isolation 22 Dec 2006 Positive
Sheep / goats virus isolation 22 Dec 2006 Positive
